{
  "level": "Grade 7 Semester 2",
  "part": "Unit 1",
  "section": "B-1b",
  "tree": {
    "id": "root",
    "text": "My Favourite Animal: The Elephant",
    "emoji": "🐘",
    "children": [
      {
        "id": "p1",
        "text": "Hi, I'm Malee and I live in Thailand!",
        "emoji": "🇹🇭",
        "keywords": "Malee, live Thailand",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "p1_1",
            "text": "The elephant is my favourite animal.",
            "emoji": "❤️",
            "keywords": "favourite animal",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "p1_2",
            "text": "I love elephants because they are strong and clever.",
            "emoji": "💪",
            "keywords": "strong, clever",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "p1_3",
            "text": "They are also a symbol of good luck here.",
            "emoji": "🍀",
            "keywords": "symbol, good luck",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "p1_4",
            "text": "The elephant is our national animal.",
            "emoji": "🏅",
            "keywords": "national animal",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "p1_5",
            "text": "On 13 March, we celebrate Thai Elephant Day.",
            "emoji": "🎉",
            "keywords": "13 March, celebrate",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "p2",
        "text": "Elephants look very different from other animals.",
        "emoji": "👀",
        "keywords": "look different",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "p2_1",
            "text": "They are huge.",
            "emoji": "⛰️",
            "keywords": "are huge",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "p2_2",
            "text": "They have large ears and long trunks.",
            "emoji": "👂",
            "keywords": "large ears, long trunks",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "p2_3",
            "text": "They can pick up and carry heavy things with their trunks.",
            "emoji": "🏋️",
            "keywords": "pick up, carry heavy",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "p3",
        "text": "Elephants are like us in some ways.",
        "emoji": "🤝",
        "keywords": "like us, some ways",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "p3_1",
            "text": "They are very playful and love to play in the water.",
            "emoji": "💦",
            "keywords": "playful, play water",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "p3_2",
            "text": "They are great swimmers.",
            "emoji": "🏊",
            "keywords": "great swimmers",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "p3_3",
            "text": "They are also clever.",
            "emoji": "🧠",
            "keywords": "also clever",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "p3_3_1",
                "text": "For example, they can remember one another and places with food and water after many years.",
                "emoji": "🗺️",
                "keywords": "remember, food, water, years",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "p3_4",
            "text": "Elephants are very kind too.",
            "emoji": "💖",
            "keywords": "very kind",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "p3_4_1",
                "text": "They look after other elephants when they don't feel well.",
                "emoji": "🏥",
                "keywords": "look after, don't feel well",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "p3_4_2",
                "text": "The big elephants also help the baby ones.",
                "emoji": "🍼",
                "keywords": "help baby ones",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "p4",
        "text": "Elephants are an important part of Thai life and culture.",
        "emoji": "🛕",
        "keywords": "important part, Thai culture",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "p4_1",
            "text": "However, they are in danger.",
            "emoji": "⚠️",
            "keywords": "in danger",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "p4_1_1",
                "text": "They live in forests, but people cut down too many trees.",
                "emoji": "🪓",
                "keywords": "forests, cut down trees",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "p4_1_2",
                "text": "People also kill elephants for their ivory.",
                "emoji": "🩸",
                "keywords": "kill for ivory",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "p4_2",
            "text": "Let's save the forests and not buy things made of ivory.",
            "emoji": "🛡️",
            "keywords": "save forests, not buy ivory",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "p4_3",
            "text": "Every elephant counts.",
            "emoji": "🔢",
            "keywords": "every elephant counts",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}